UNFOLDING and INTERPOLATION of bands from a supercell calculation at Gamma only.


TODO:
- smooth interpolation
- parallelization


The code has to be run in the directory where the Wannier90 output is
('seedname.wout' and 'wf_phases.dat'). The 'input_ui.json' file has to be
the same directory.

The input Koopmans or Wannier90 hamiltoanian is passed as arg:

		python3 ~/path-to-ui-code/unf_int.py file_ham


The code can also be run in an interactive way.
The class Parse_Data in parser.py module allows to define an instance
having all the important quanities as attributes.

Then the code can be run sequentially as follows:

1)		data = Parse_Data()
		data.parse_data('file_ham')

Parse_Data defines the instance 'data' and then parse_data calls all the
functions (parse_json, parse_w90, parse_hr, parse_phases) which assign
all the input data as attributes of 'data'.

2)		map_wannier(data)
		calc_bands(data)
		calc_dos(data)

These three functions:
 - build the map |i> -> |Rn>
 - interpolate H(k) and calculate the electron energies
 - calculate the density-of-states
respectively.

3)		write_results(data)

Writes the results to file: 'bands_interpolated.dat' and
'dos_interpolated.dat' in the Quantum Espresso format.	
